echoflow (0.2.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a first-run guide that downloads the selected speech model, enables
    the user services, verifies Fcitx readiness, and resumes or retries
    incomplete setup without losing diagnostic details.
  * Make the usage guide available from the tray and settings so users can
    revisit the recording shortcut, privacy model, and configuration entry
    points at any time.
  * Refresh onboarding with image-led pages, an application title bar, and a
    native DTK setup group that remains accessible in light and dark themes.
  * Harden single-instance activation so desktop launches reliably reach the
    existing UI process during startup and reject unsafe socket responses.
  * Improve local and Debian upgrades with an installed desktop launcher,
    desktop-file validation, and coordinated service restarts after updates.
  * Publish a project landing page with the current offline voice-input
    workflow and installation entry points.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 21:41:13 +0800

echoflow (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rework the voice capsule so it appears only while recording or
    transcribing, with a cancel (X) button and a stop-and-transcribe
    (check) button instead of the old focus-tracking idle hint.
  * Redesign the recording waveform as a compact symbolic indicator that
    sits beside the live text, replacing the loud scaling bars.
  * Improve speech endpointing so the last phrase of a dictation is no
    longer cut off, and keep quiet and boundary speech from being dropped.
  * Smooth the capsule's appear and state transitions by removing the
    width animation that forced expensive per-frame background blur.
  * Reject stale partial text after a capture failure so corrupted audio
    never reaches the committed output.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 23:42:04 +0800

echoflow (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add live and segmented Qwen transcription so recognition can progress
    during recording and long dictation returns stable text sooner.
  * Add microphone source selection with friendly device names and a fallback
    source query so users can choose the intended PipeWire input reliably.
  * Add a stream mode switch and live text preview in the voice capsule while
    keeping final committed text based on completed recognition.
  * Apply settings changes by restarting the service and hide unavailable
    microphones to prevent silent recordings from disconnected inputs.
  * Improve speech detection for quiet or DC-offset microphone audio and make
    live recording shutdown bounded when workers or PipeWire cleanup stall.
  * Add an EchoFlow tray logo and remove unused recognition settings from the
    settings dialog.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:29:29 +0800

echoflow (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of EchoFlow, an offline voice input method for
    deepin/Fcitx5 powered by the Qwen ASR runtime.
  * Download and manage 0.6B/1.7B Qwen ASR models directly from the
    settings UI, replacing the legacy setup script.
  * Toggle recording with right-Ctrl and get visual feedback through an
    animated capsule tooltip near the cursor.
  * DTK-integrated settings dialog that follows system theme colors.
  * Native C++17 service with tuned ASR startup and OpenBLAS latency.
  * CMake-backed Debian packaging with a GitHub Actions release workflow.

 -- Hualet Wang <hualet@deepin.org>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 09:30:00 +0800
